    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-12T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-12T12:00:00-05:00" n="730"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d730fn1">Repeated to Canberra as telegram 246.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-12T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 12, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 406. It seems clear from Canberra’s 290
                    rptd <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 371,<note n="2" xml:id="d730fn2"
                        >Dated June 8. <ref target="#pg_1062">p. 1062</ref>.</note> other messages
                    from <persName corresp="#p_PAJ1">Peaslee</persName> and talks here with
                        <persName corresp="#p_CSWLS1">Spencer</persName> that Australians are
                    convinced of the need for developing collective arrangements for Southeast Asia
                    area. With recent development in <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>’s
                    position, it should be easier for Australia and New Zealand to assist in
                    carrying project forward and I am sure <persName corresp="#p_CRG1"
                        >Casey</persName>’s return to Geneva will give you opportunity to enlist his
                    aid. I understand he plans return home via Washington and in your discretion
                    tell him I am delighted he plans stop in Washington and will look forward to
                    opportunity of good discussions with him. Suggest to him that he let me know his
                    plans as soon as they are firm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
